race.comment: ETERNAL EMBER (5) is speedy and followed her debut win at Wagga Riverside with a solid placing in a CL1 at the Sapphire Coast. Finds easier with a 3kg claim and fitter again, she should be winning in this company. ABSTRUSE (2) wasn't beaten far at Wagga and went close at Moruya prior. Better suited and the extra metres suit her. SHELLY'S ACE (8) finished second at Canberra two runs back this grade but didn't measure up last time there following in a strong form race at 55 level. The 2kg claimer will use the inside barrier, and a much sharper effort is likely. DRAMA DODGER (3) resumes for Canberra's Kirkup yard and goes well fresh. Has a low gate and a 2kg claim and is a chance if presented on song.
